<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100224606097685></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100224606097685><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=item.html?item=5402&mid=100224606097685>Azzar's Dreadful Hat....</a> <a id=fs8 href=item.html?item=5402&mid=100224606097685#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=104254><span id= >IgorIsDeadSexy</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>10 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Oct 4th 9:41 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Ok, here is my 2 cents to add to the info.<br><br>I have spent lvls 20-24 in the Warrens and Stonebrunt, so I have gone by this Cave Bat Lord many a time (i think he has killed me once or twice too).&nbsp;&nbsp;I didn't attempt to start killing him until just recently.  I have now killed him about 4 or 5 times on my way through the Warrens.  The last time I killed him he dropped the hat.  I was 23 at the time... (actually hit 24 from killing him).<br><br>He is pretty easy to kill at 23 or 24 for any class.  The bats around him should not aggro at that level... and he is a fairly simple kill. <br><br>When I kill him I usually pull him into that big wide open room between his room and the kings room, and fight along the edge to avoid starting a train.<br><br>So far I have had no problems killing him, no tricks up his sleeve or anything.  He seems that he drops the hat once out of every 5-10 times you kill him.  I got it in 5 attempts.<br><br>Good Luck all,<br><br>Zaggore Tramane<br>24th Enchanter<br>Fennin Ro<br>Diamond Phoenix<br><br> <br>&nbsp;<br>It may take 42 muscles to frown, but it only takes 4 to pull the trigger on a well made sniper rifle</td></tr>
